The paper deals with the problem of privacy-preserving data publication, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The use of differential privacy to protect the privacy of participants is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the cryptography and security community (cs.CR). The proposed algorithms involve statistical techniques such as EM and Lasso regression, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the challenges of high-dimensional data, which is a topic of interest in the data science community (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves information theory, which is a topic of interest in the information theory community (cs.IT).
